messages.body:
$CHWY Love this company, the website, the customer service, and the overall idea, including telehealth component. 

That last is a gamechanger. Vet visits are a HUGE hassle, sometimes needed only for annual heartworm prescription. 

Not saying that heartworm check or pyoderma (dog skin problem) check can be done virtually. But is there room for disruption? Heck yes

Then again, vets and pet industry, including dog food (AAFCO) are notoriously regulated. Not unlike insurance industry ($ROOT, $LMND) or orthodontics ($SDC, $ALGN)
